    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "PSA\nNZIPS\nElectra JET\nPSA",
      "PSA- - PACIFIC SOUTHWEST AIRLINES\nLockheed L-188C Electra\nPSA, then an intra-state airline operating wholly with-\n(shown\nisnown on this california November\nreceived its first Electra\nthis card).\n1959.\nIn a few\nyears, PSA became the dominant air carrier in\nthe\nState, much of\nits success being attributed\npopularity\nand\nreliability\nof\nto\nthe\nthe Electra. In\nthe airline\nsold its entire\n1968\nElectra\nfleet,\nthem\nwith\n727's.\nreplacing\nThis particular Electra was\npurchased in 1975 for\nre-\nuse\non a newly\nawarded\nroute\nwhich was unsuitable for currently\navailable\npure jet aircraft.\nPhoto courtesy Lockheed-California Company\nPub. by Aviation World, Inc., P.O. Box 188, Bethel, Conn. 06801, U.S.A.\nN171PS c/n 1091\nL-009/61036-D\npost card\n2015.\n.1195"
    ],
